<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1037683>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 - 1. Ocypus (Pseudocypus) pileaticulminis sp. nov.: A. habitus of species (2.0 mm); B. aedeagus, lateral view; (0.5 mm); C. aedeagus, ventral view (0.5 mm); D. underside of apical portion of paramere (0.5 mm); E. second gonocoxite of female genital segment (0.5 mm). Scale in parentheses." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1037683/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1037691>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2 - 3. Ocypus (Pseudocypus) denticulminis sp. nov.: A, B and C: variations of teeth on mandibles (1.0 mm); D. habitus of one of the special large specimens collected together with Ocypus (Pseudocypus) persiciculminis sp. nov. (2.0 mm). Scale in parentheses." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1037691/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1037685>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 - 2. Ocypus (Pseudocypus) pileaticulminis sp. nov.: A. male tergite 10; B and D. aedeagus, lateral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view; E. female tergite 10; F. apical portion of median lobe, ventral view, paramere removed; G. underside of apical portion of paramere; H. male sternite 9; I. second gonocoxite of female genital segment; J. male sternite 8. Scale bars = 0.50 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1037685/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

